---
import BioLanguageToggle from '../components/BioLanguageToggle.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/url';
---
<BaseLayout title="Press & Media Kit" description="Bio, headshots, and press materials for Juraci Paixão Kröhling.">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="pageheader">
      <h1>Press & Media Kit</h1>
      <p class="meta">Everything an event organizer needs — bios in three languages, headshots, and a one-liner.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Bio</h2>
        <BioLanguageToggle />
      </div>
      <div class="prose" data-bio-lang="en">
        <p>Juraci Paixão Kröhling is CEO of OllyGarden, a Governance Committee member for the OpenTelemetry project, and an emeritus maintainer of the OpenTelemetry Collector and the Jaeger project. With a deep expertise in observability and open-source development, he has spoken at leading conferences such as KubeCon EU, KubeCon NA, OpenSource Summit, Devoxx Belgium, FOSDEM, and multiple DevOpsDays events.</p>
        <p>Passionate about distributed tracing and observability, Juraci helps software engineers build reliable observability pipelines and optimize their applications. He started and maintained several open-source projects along the way, including the Jaeger Operator, the OpenTelemetry Operator, the OpenTelemetry Collector Builder (OCB), and the load-balancing exporter. He is also co-founder of Telemetry Drops, an OpenTelemetry training program for engineers and teams.</p>
        <p>Outside of work, Juraci is a proud parent of three kids and finds solace in the hobby of sleeping, albeit occasionally interrupted by the delightful chaos of parenting responsibilities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose" data-bio-lang="de" hidden lang="de">
        <p>Juraci Paixão Kröhling ist CEO von OllyGarden, Mitglied des Governance-Komitees für das OpenTelemetry-Projekt und emeritierter Maintainer des OpenTelemetry Collectors und des Jaeger-Projekts. Mit fundierter Expertise in Observability und Open-Source-Entwicklung hat er auf führenden Konferenzen wie KubeCon EU, KubeCon NA, OpenSource Summit, Devoxx Belgium, FOSDEM und mehreren DevOpsDays-Events gesprochen.</p>
        <p>Als leidenschaftlicher Experte für verteiltes Tracing und Observability unterstützt Juraci Softwareentwickler dabei, zuverlässige Observability-Pipelines aufzubauen und ihre Anwendungen zu optimieren. Er hat zahlreiche Open-Source-Projekte in diesem Bereich ins Leben gerufen und gepflegt — darunter den Jaeger Operator, den OpenTelemetry Operator, den OpenTelemetry Collector Builder (OCB) und den Load-Balancing Exporter. Er ist außerdem Mitgründer von Telemetry Drops, einem OpenTelemetry-Trainingsprogramm für Entwicklerinnen, Entwickler und Teams.</p>
        <p>Abseits der Arbeit ist Juraci stolzer Vater von drei Kindern und findet Erholung in seinem liebsten Hobby – dem Schlafen –, auch wenn dies gelegentlich von der wunderbaren, aber turbulenten Realität des Elternseins unterbrochen wird.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose" data-bio-lang="pt" hidden lang="pt">
        <p>Juraci Paixão Kröhling é CEO da OllyGarden, membro do Comitê de Governança do projeto OpenTelemetry e mantenedor emérito do OpenTelemetry Collector e do projeto Jaeger. Com uma profunda experiência em observabilidade e desenvolvimento open-source, ele já palestrou em conferências de renome, como KubeCon EU, KubeCon NA, OpenSource Summit, Devoxx Belgium, FOSDEM e diversos eventos do DevOpsDays.</p>
        <p>Apaixonado por tracing distribuído e observabilidade, Juraci ajuda engenheiros de software a construir pipelines de observabilidade confiáveis e a otimizar suas aplicações. Ele iniciou e manteve diversos projetos open-source nessa área — entre eles o Jaeger Operator, o OpenTelemetry Operator, o OpenTelemetry Collector Builder (OCB) e o load-balancing exporter. Também é co-fundador da Telemetry Drops, um programa de treinamento em OpenTelemetry para engenheiros e times.</p>
        <p>Fora do trabalho, Juraci é um pai orgulhoso de três filhos e encontra descanso em seu hobby favorito – dormir –, embora isso ocasionalmente seja interrompido pelo adorável caos das responsabilidades parentais.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>One-liner</h2>
      <blockquote class="oneliner">
        <p>Juraci Paixão Kröhling — CEO of OllyGarden, OpenTelemetry Governance Committee member, emeritus maintainer of the OpenTelemetry Collector and Jaeger.</p>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Headshots</h2>
      <ul class="headshots">
        <li>
          <a href={withBase('/press-assets/profile.webp')} download>
            <img src={withBase('/press-assets/profile-small.png')} alt="Headshot, plain background" loading="lazy" />
            <span class="thumb-meta">
              <span class="thumb-name">profile</span>
              <span class="thumb-fmt">.webp · .png</span>
            </span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href={withBase('/press-assets/profile-background.webp')} download>
            <img src={withBase('/press-assets/profile-background-small.png')} alt="Headshot with background" loading="lazy" />
            <span class="thumb-meta">
              <span class="thumb-name">profile-background</span>
              <span class="thumb-fmt">.webp · .png</span>
            </span>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="meta">All headshots are also available in the <a href="https://github.com/jpkrohling/talks/tree/main/headshots">repository's headshots folder</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
  .container { padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-16); }
  .pageheader { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .section { padding-block: var(--space-6); border-top: 1px solid var(--cream-200); }
  .section-head { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .oneliner { background: var(--cream-50); border-left: 3px solid var(--bordeaux-700); padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6); margin: 0; border-radius: var(--radius-card); }
  .oneliner p { margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.125rem; font-style: italic; }
  .headshots { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(14rem, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-4); }
  .headshots a { display: block; background: var(--cream-50); border: 1px solid var(--cream-200); border-radius: var(--radius-card); overflow: hidden; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.18s var(--ease-out); }
  .headshots a:hover { border-color: var(--bordeaux-700); }
  .headshots img { width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 1 / 1; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
  .thumb-meta { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3); font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: 0.8125rem; }
  .thumb-name { font-weight: 600; }
  .thumb-fmt { color: var(--ink-400); font-size: 0.75rem; }
</style>
